# Code formatting

Use the root Prettier config (`.prettierrc`). Do not override style per file.

## Style

- Single quotes in JS/TS (`singleQuote: true`); double quotes in JSX attributes (`jsxSingleQuote: false`).
- Semicolons on; trailing commas `all`; print width 100; 2-space indent; LF endings.
- One JSX/HTML attribute per line (`singleAttributePerLine`).
- Tailwind classes sorted via `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss`.

## Imports

Prettier (`@ianvs/prettier-plugin-sort-imports`) orders imports as:

1. `react` / `react-dom`
2. `@nestjs/*`
3. Node builtins
4. Third-party packages
5. `@velon/*` workspace packages
6. `@/*` web absolute paths
7. Relative imports (`./`, `../`)

Keep type-only imports as `import type` where appropriate. Prefer `@/` on the web over deep relative paths.

## Commands

```bash
npm run format        # write
npm run format:check  # CI / verify
```

Run format on touched files before finishing a change set when style would otherwise drift.
